directory: crates
domain: Workspace root holding every first-party crate of the CTX system: enforced file access (ctx-access), sandboxed agent execution (ctx-cage), the canonical access-gate logic (ctx-core), the `.context/` summary pipeline (ctx-scan, ctx-summarize), context-chain rendering/hooks (ctx-context), and two independent check-running CLIs (ctx-check, ctx-verify). This directory itself holds no source; it is the dependency graph between these crates.
edit_notes:
  - ctx-core's access.rs is the single canonical secret/binary/gitignored deny gate; ctx-access delegates to it entirely — any denylist logic added elsewhere in these crates is a bug, not a feature.
  - The `.context/<src>.ctx` / `.context/<dir>/rollup.ctx` path layout is independently implemented in both ctx-summarize (cpath.rs) and ctx-access; a pending unification into ctx-core means both must be changed together until that lands.
  - ctx-scan drives ctx-summarize's runner for staleness-triggered regeneration, and ctx-context/ctx-access both read the same rollup/intent/leaf chain that ctx-summarize writes — chain ordering or file-naming changes ripple through all three.
  - ctx-check and ctx-verify are separate crates with overlapping purpose (both run cargo/clippy/script checks and emit a capped JSON pass/fail report); changes to one's check set or report shape do not propagate to the other automatically.
children:
  - ctx-access: Enforcement gateway — the only sanctioned read/write/list path into repo files for agents, delegating access decisions to ctx-core.
  - ctx-cage: Sandbox launcher wrapping agent sessions in bwrap, with host-side proxy as sole network egress.
  - ctx-check: Verification broker CLI producing a capped JSON check report.
  - ctx-context: Renders and injects the rollup/intent/leaf context chain for a given path, including a Claude Code session hook.
  - ctx-core: Zero-dependency source of the access-gate rules consumed by ctx-access (and intended for wider reuse).
  - ctx-scan: Maintains `.context/` freshness via content hashing and triggers ctx-summarize regeneration.
  - ctx-summarize: Generates leaf `.ctx` and `rollup.ctx` files consumed by ctx-scan, ctx-context, and ctx-access.
  - ctx-verify: Separate fixed-check-set CLI emitting its own capped JSON verification report.
invariants:
  - Every crate isolates real filesystem/process/clock access behind an injected seam (Env/Fs/Runner/Agent) with fake implementations exercised in tests — no crate's core logic touches the OS directly.
  - `.context/` scaffolding (rollup.ctx, intent.md, per-file .ctx) is the only artifact shared as a cross-crate contract; none of these crates serve